Anne Haddy https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anne_Haddy 0 Anne Haddy (5 October 1930 – 6 June 1999), was an Australian actress, who worked in all facets of the industry including radio, stage, television and film, she was best known for her television soap roles as Alice Hemmings in cult series Prisoner, Rosie Andrews on Sons and Daughters and matriarch Helen Daniels in the long-running Australian soap opera, Neighbours.
